1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO DRIVER EDUCATION; REQUIRING DRIVER EDUCATION
3 COURSES AND SCHOOLS TO INCLUDE AT LEAST THREE HOURS OF
4 EDUCATION AND TRAINING ON DRIVING WITH VULNERABLE ROAD USERS.
5
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF NEW MEXICO:
7 SECTION 1. Section 22-13-12 NMSA 1978 (being Laws 1967,
8 Chapter 16, Section 186, as amended) is amended to read:
9 "22-13-12. APPROVED DRIVER-EDUCATION COURSES.--
10 A. The department or its designated representative
11 shall adopt and promulgate minimum standards for approved
12 driver-education and motorcycle driver-education courses
13 taught in any school in the state, which shall include at
14 least three hours of education and training on driving with
15 vulnerable road users.
16 B. A driver-education or motorcycle
17 driver-education course shall provide to students legally
18 entitled to operate the type of motor vehicle involved
19 classroom instruction and behind-the-wheel or on-the-
20 motorcycle training in the safe operation of the motor
21 vehicle.
22 C. An approved driver-education or motorcycle
23 driver-education course is a course of instruction certified
24 by the secretary as meeting the minimum standards for a
25 driver-education course adopted by the department or its SB 73
Page 1

1 designated representative.
2 D. As used in this section, "vulnerable road user"
3 includes:
4 (a) a pedestrian, including a person engaged
5 in work or in the provision of emergency services upon or
6 along a roadway;
7 (b) a person riding or leading an animal; or
8 (c) a person lawfully operating or riding a
9 bicycle, tricycle or other pedal-powered vehicle, a farm
10 tractor or similar vehicle designed primarily for farm use, a
11 skateboard, a scooter, a moped, a motorcycle, roller skates,
12 inline skates, an animal-drawn wheeled vehicle, an electric
13 personal assistive mobility device, a wheelchair or another
14 similar means of transportation in which the person is not
15 surrounded by a shell of protection such as that which a car
16 or truck provides."
17 SECTION 2. Section 66-1-4.19 NMSA 1978 (being Laws
18 1990, Chapter 120, Section 20, as amended) is amended to
19 read:
20 "66-1-4.19. DEFINITIONS.--As used in the Motor Vehicle
21 Code:
22 A. "validating sticker" means the tab or sticker
23 issued by the division to signify, upon a registration plate,
24 renewed registration;
25 B. "vehicle" means every device in, upon or by SB 73
Page 2

1 which any person or property is or may be transported or
2 drawn upon a highway, including any frame, chassis, body or
3 unitized frame and body of any vehicle or motor vehicle,
4 except devices moved exclusively by human power or used
5 exclusively upon stationary rails or tracks;
6 C. "vehicle-business number" means the distinctive
7 registration number given by the division to any
8 manufacturer, auto recycler or dealer;
9 D. "vehicle plate" means a plate, marker, sticker
10 or tag similar to a registration plate, but that is issued by
11 the department for vehicles that are exempted from
12 registration under the Motor Vehicle Code;
13 E. "verification process" means a method of
14 authenticating an electronic credential through the use of
15 secure and encrypted communication; and
16 F. "vulnerable road user" includes:
17 (a) a pedestrian, including a person engaged
18 in work or in the provision of emergency services upon or
19 along a roadway;
20 (b) a person riding or leading an animal; or
21 (c) a person lawfully operating or riding a
22 bicycle, tricycle or other pedal-powered vehicle, a farm
23 tractor or similar vehicle designed primarily for farm use, a
24 skateboard, a scooter, a moped, a motorcycle, roller skates,
25 inline skates, an animal-drawn wheeled vehicle, an electric SB 73
