1 personal assistive mobility device, a wheelchair or another
2 similar means of transportation in which the person is not
3 surrounded by a shell of protection such as that which a car
4 or truck provides."
5 SECTION 3. Section 66-7-506 NMSA 1978 (being Laws 1978,
6 Chapter 35, Section 493, as amended) is amended to read:
7 "66-7-506. BUREAU--FUNCTIONS--POWERS--DUTIES.--The
8 bureau shall have the following powers and duties:
9 A. organize, plan and conduct a statewide program
10 of activities designed to prevent accidents and to reduce the
11 incidence of DWI in New Mexico;
12 B. coordinate activities and programs of the
13 departments, divisions and agencies of this state now engaged
14 in promoting traffic safety;
15 C. provide accident prevention information and
16 publicity to all appropriate media of information and develop
17 other means of public information;
18 D. cooperate with all public and private agencies
19 and organizations interested in the promotion of traffic
20 safety and accident prevention;
21 E. serve as a clearinghouse for all traffic safety
22 materials and information used throughout this state;
23 F. cooperate in promoting research, special
24 studies and analysis of problems concerning the safety and
25 welfare of the citizens of New Mexico; SB 73
Page 4

1 G. cooperate fully with national safety
2 organizations in bringing about greater effectiveness in
3 nationwide accident prevention activities and programs;
4 H. make studies and suitable recommendations,
5 through the chief and the secretary of transportation, to the
6 legislature concerning safety regulations and laws;
7 I. prepare and submit each year a written report
8 to the governor concerning the activities of the bureau and
9 activities concerning assistance to local organizations and
10 officials;
11 J. institute and administer a statewide motorcycle
12 training program funded as provided for in Section 66-10-10
13 NMSA 1978;
14 K. institute and administer an accident prevention
15 course for elderly drivers as provided for in Section
16 59A-32-14 NMSA 1978;
17 L. cooperate with the public education department
18 to develop a regulatory framework for instructional and
19 administrative processes, including licensure requirements
20 for instructors, and a curriculum for instruction in
21 defensive driving with a DWI education and prevention
22 component to be offered statewide in secondary schools as an
23 elective;
24 M. institute and administer a DWI prevention and
25 education program for elementary and secondary school SB 73
Page 5

1 students, funded as provided for in Section 66-5-35 NMSA
2 1978;
3 N. prescribe minimum driver education and training
4 program standards pursuant to the Driving School Licensing
5 Act; and
6 O. include a DWI recidivism prevention component
7 in all driver rehabilitation programs for alcohol or drugs
8 approved by the bureau."
9 SECTION 4. Section 66-10-5 NMSA 1978 (being Laws 1967,
10 Chapter 185, Section 5, as amended) is amended to read:
11 "66-10-5. ISSUANCE OF LICENSES TO DRIVER EDUCATION
12 SCHOOLS AND TO DRIVER EDUCATION INSTRUCTORS.--
13 A. The bureau shall issue a license certificate to
14 each applicant to conduct a driver education school or to
15 each driver education instructor when it is satisfied that
16 the person has met the qualifications required under the
17 Driving School Licensing Act and if a school complies with
18 the minimum driver education program standards established by
19 the bureau.
20 B. The bureau shall prescribe minimum driver
21 training program standards, which shall include:
22 (1) at least two hours of DWI prevention and
23 education training; and
24 (2) at least three hours of education and
25 training on driving with vulnerable road users. SB 73
Page 6

1 C. All licenses issued pursuant to the provisions
2 of the Driving School Licensing Act shall expire annually,
3 unless canceled, suspended or revoked sooner. The bureau
4 shall establish annual expiration dates for the licenses by
5 rule, and each category of driving school may have a
6 different license expiration date. Licenses shall be renewed
7 subject to application and payment of the required fee."
8 SECTION 5. EFFECTIVE DATE.--The effective date of the
9 provisions of this act is January 1, 2027. SB 73
